  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency response to drought conditions in Somalia through access to clean safe water, sanitation and hygiene services in Lower Juba and Gedo.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this IOM project is to improve and sustain access to clean water, sanitation and hygiene for communities affected by drought conditions in Lower Juba and Gedo regions of Somalia. 
With this 1.9 million USD CERF grant, IOM will provide access to safe drinking water to 60,000 people, provide 12,083 hygiene kits and will construct 600 latrines. 
The project covers WASH sector and will last six months. It will benefit 72,500 persons including 19,937 girls and 19,938 women.</narrative>
  </description>
